Add the Input Widget to Formula Queries

Retrieving values from the input widget to use in a formula can be done through the UI. You can add the input widget as a column in a query or with SAQL.

Steps:
Use the input widget to build a formula in a new or existing query.
Add an input widget to your dashboard, create a query or select an existing one for building your formula, edit the query and add a column selecting Input, search and select an input query, add another column selecting Formula, use the formula editor to create a calculation using values from the input query.

Add the Input Widget to a SAQL Query

Add the input widget to a new or existing query using SAQL.
Steps:
Add an input widget to your dashboard, create a query or select an existing one for building your formula, edit the query and click Query Mode, position your cursor in the SAQL code where to add values from the input query, and click the Add Input link.
title: Adding Input Widget to Formula Queries in CRM Analytics
